physical_appearance: This is a black-and-white photograph. It is rectangular in shape and portrait in orientation. The photograph features two women, posing in the center. They are both wearing mid-lengthed dresses with collars. They are standing in the middle of a road. On the right, there are several other people walking on the road. In the background of the photograph, there is a large building seen.
sgcool_label_text: This is a personal photograph album that belonged to a Corporal A. Silver who spent 16 months in Singapore between 1951 and 1952. Silver was presumably a Jewish lady who was stationed in Singapore to serve at the Royal Air Force (RAF) Hospital at Changi. The album contains photographs that document her working and personal life, including friends she made within the Jewish community in Singapore.
title_text: "Personal photograph album titled ""Sixteen Months in Singapore""" Sixteen Months in Singapore: Photograph of Corporal A. Silver with woman  in front of building
